#### Document Numbering System Updates (January 2025)

**Organisation-Based Document Numbering Implementation:**
- **Root Cause Resolution**: Fixed "Document type configuration not found" errors by implementing organisation-based document numbering
- **Database Schema**: Updated document type configurations to use organisations as the primary entity instead of companies
- **SQL Migration**: Created `populate-all-document-types-for-companies.sql` script to populate document types for all organisations
- **Frontend Updates**: Modified UpsertFileModal to use organisation dropdown instead of company dropdown
- **API Integration**: Updated document numbering service calls to use organisation IDs
- **Schema Compliance**: Handles mixed British/American spelling conventions (organisations table, organization_id column)

**Key Changes:**
- Document types are now configured at the organisation level (the correct entity for document numbering)
- All 7 standard document types (Claim, Contract Agreement, Correspondence, Minutes of Meeting, Request for Quotation, Site Instruction, Variation Notice) are created for each organisation
- Frontend forms now display "Organisation" instead of "Company" for document uploads
- Document numbering preview and generation use organisation-based parameters
- Proper foreign key relationships maintained with valid company_id references

**Files Modified:**
- `client/src/pages/00435-contracts-post-award/components/modals/00435-02-UpsertFileModal.js` - Updated to use organisations
- `populate-all-document-types-for-companies.sql` - SQL script for populating document types
- `client/src/services/documentNumberingService.js` - Service integration
- `server/api/document-numbering/` - Backend API endpoints

**Impact:**
- Resolves document numbering configuration errors
- Provides consistent organisation-based document management
- Maintains backward compatibility with existing data structures
- Enables proper document number generation for all organisations

