#### 0250\_ - Utilities Architecture

- Utility scripts and tools
  - String manipulation and formatting
  - Cookie management
  - File handling utilities
- Path resolution and services
    - Webpack Configuration:
      - Manages the bundling of JavaScript, CSS, HTML, and other assets for the client-side application.
      - The project has transitioned to a Single-Page Application (SPA) structure, with webpack configured for a single entry point and dynamic content rendering via React.
      - Key aspects of the configuration include a single entry point, output management (to `client/dist2/`), various loaders for different file types (JavaScript/JSX, CSS, assets), an extensive set of plugins (e.g., `HtmlWebpackPlugin`, `MiniCssExtractPlugin`, `CopyWebpackPlugin`), and a development server setup.
      - For a high-level overview of webpack's role and best practices in this project, see [1500 Webpack Architecture](./1500_WEBPACK_ARCHITECTURE.md).
      - For a detailed explanation of the `client/config/webpack.config.js` file and its specific settings, see [1510 Webpack Configuration File Details](./1510_WEBPACK_CONFIGURATION_FILE.md).

